      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/render.ts",
      "title": "Unused _cols parameter in renderReviewSection",
      "detail": "The `cols` parameter was renamed to `_cols` indicating it's unused, but the review section content (Round line with multiple parts joined) could exceed terminal width. The existing truncation may happen at the frame level via padEndVisible, but worth confirming the Round line is bounded. Low priority since padEndVisible handles it.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 3,
      "status": "open",
      "relation": "same",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R2-F05",
      "severity": "low",
      "category": "quality",
      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/model.ts",
      "title": "loop_state typed as string but design says string | null",
      "detail": "Design Contracts show `loop_state: string | null` in ReviewRoundView, but the implementation types it as `string` (from the existing definition). The manualFixFallback sets it to `\"\"`. Minor mismatch — empty string vs null semantics differ. The completed badge check `loop_state ? ` handles both, so no functional bug, but consider aligning with the design contract.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 3,
      "status": "open",
      "relation": "same",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R2-F03",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "testing",
      "file": "src/tests/specflow-watch-launcher.test.ts",
      "title": "Launcher tests exist but are not included in the diff",
      "detail": "The file `src/tests/specflow-watch-launcher.test.ts` is listed as untracked in git status but its content is not part of this diff. The design explicitly requires launcher behavior-level tests (PATH stub, env control, command string verification, quoting, PID fallthrough). Ensure this file is staged and included in the changeset. Without it, the launcher's cross-platform dispatch logic has zero automated test coverage — a high-severity gap given the number of emulator branches.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 3,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "reframed",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R3-F01",
      "severity": "low",
      "category": "testing",
      "file": "src/tests/specflow-watch-launcher.test.ts",
      "title": "No test for screen ($STY) or $TERMINAL branches",
      "detail": "The launcher tests cover gnome-terminal, kitty, wezterm, xterm, manual fallback, and PID-death fallthrough, but do not test the `$STY` (screen) or `$TERMINAL` environment-variable branches. These are lower-priority since they use the same `_try_bg` / `&&` patterns already tested, but adding coverage would strengthen confidence.",
      "origin_round": 3,
      "latest_round": 3,
      "status": "open",
      "relation": "reframed",
      "supersedes": "R2-F03",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R3-F02",
      "severity": "low",
      "category": "correctness",
      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/model.ts",
      "title": "Design doc field name deviation: manual_fix_open_count → ReviewManualFixIndicator",
      "detail": "design.md specifies `ReviewRoundView.manual_fix_open_count: number | null` but the implementation uses a tagged union `ReviewManualFixIndicator { active: boolean; count: number | null }`. The tagged union is arguably a better API (distinguishes idle from active-with-null-count), but differs from the design doc. Consider updating design.md to match.",
      "origin_round": 3,
      "latest_round": 3,
      "status": "new",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R3-F03",
      "severity": "low",
      "category": "scope",
      "file": "assets/commands/specflow.md.tmpl",
      "title": "Duplicated launch_watch function across two templates",
      "detail": "The exact same ~70-line `launch_watch()` Bash function is duplicated in both `specflow.md.tmpl` and `specflow.watch.md.tmpl`. The proposal mentions a shared helper (`src/lib/specflow-watch-launcher.ts`), but the implementation inlines the shell function in both templates. This is intentional per the template-based architecture (templates are standalone), but any future change requires updating both copies. The launcher test already validates the `specflow.watch.md.tmpl` copy, and snapshot tests catch drift.",
      "origin_round": 3,
      "latest_round": 3,
      "status": "new",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R2-F01",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "completeness",
      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/model.ts",
      "title": "D5 both-null case diverges from design table",
      "detail": "Design.md D5 table row \"ファイル存在・両方なし（malformed）\" specifies that when both status_line and diffstat_line are null, the view builder should escalate to `{ kind: \"warning\", message: \"Approval summary malformed\" }`. The implementation instead renders `Status: (unknown)` with null diffstat (a valid ok result). The code comment explicitly says this is intentional ('Both fields missing is still a valid render … rather than a malformed warning'). However, this contradicts the design table. Either the design table or the implementation should be updated to match. Since the implementation behavior is arguably more user-friendly (still shows something), consider updating the design table if this was a deliberate override.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 2,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R2-F02",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "completeness",
      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/model.ts",
      "title": "ReviewRoundView uses manual_fix instead of spec's manual_fix_open_count",
      "detail": "Design.md Contracts section defines `ReviewRoundView.manual_fix_open_count: number | null` but the implementation uses a tagged union `manual_fix: ReviewManualFixIndicator = { active: false } | { active: true, count: number | null }`. This is functionally richer and arguably better, but it's a contract deviation. If intentional (which seems likely given better ergonomics), update the design's Contracts section to match the actual type.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 2,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R2-F06",
      "severity": "low",
      "category": "scope",
      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/model.ts",
      "title": "eventSummary adds gate_ref from ev.gate_ref top-level field",
      "detail": "The eventSummary function reads `ev.gate_ref` as a top-level field on RawObservationEvent, but the spec's gate_opened scenario says 'if gate_ref is non-empty, append (gate_ref)'. Confirm `gate_ref` is actually a top-level field on RawObservationEvent (not only in payload). The code works for both locations but the type access pattern should match the actual data shape.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 2,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R2-F07",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "testing",
      "file": "src/tests/specflow-watch-integration.test.ts",
      "title": "No integration test for manual-fix badge or approval summary",
      "detail": "The design's Completion Conditions (C4, C6) require integration tests with fixtures for manual fix and approval summary. The integration test file was updated to fix the existing selector test but doesn't add new integration tests for: (1) manual-fix badge appearing/disappearing based on history, (2) approval summary rendering from a real fixture file. The unit tests in watch-renderer.test.ts cover the model layer well, but the integration gap means the full buildModel→renderFrame pipeline for these features is untested.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 2,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F01",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "error_handling",
      "file": "src/lib/specflow-watch/artifact-readers.ts",
      "title": "Missing approval-summary file is rendered as 'No approval yet'",
      "detail": "The spec distinguishes `last_summary_path == null` (`No approval yet`) from `last_summary_path` pointing at a missing file (`Approval summary missing` warning). `readApprovalSummary()` returns `absent` for both cases, so a broken or moved summary silently looks like no approval happened. Return a distinct missing-file state, or pass enough context into the renderer to emit the required warning.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F02",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "error_handling",
      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/model.ts",
      "title": "Manual-fix fallback drops to warning when the snapshot is unreadable",
      "detail": "The proposal requires manual-fix mode to stay visible and render `? unresolved` whenever the family snapshot cannot be read. `buildReviewView()` only does that for `snapshot.kind === \"absent\"`; `unreadable` and `malformed` still return warning states, so the required manual-fix indicator disappears instead of degrading to the specified placeholder-style output.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F03",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "correctness",
      "file": "src/lib/watch-renderer/model.ts",
      "title": "All-missing approval summaries are treated as malformed instead of `Status: (unknown)`",
      "detail": "The spec says a missing `Status:` line should degrade to `Status: (unknown)`, and a missing diffstat should simply omit the second line. `buildApprovalSummary()` currently turns `{ status_line: null, diffstat_line: null }` into `Approval summary malformed`, which violates that fallback contract. Normalize this case to `Status: (unknown)` with no diffstat line.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F04",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "testing",
      "file": "src/tests/watch-renderer.test.ts",
      "title": "The new tests lock in the wrong approval-summary fallback behavior",
      "detail": "The added coverage asserts that both missing fields should produce a malformed warning, which is the opposite of the proposal's `Status: (unknown)` fallback. Update the tests to enforce the actual contract, and add a case for `last_summary_path` present but file missing so the required warning path is covered.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
